OL,3,CMan who set up traps and explosives
OL,4,C'inspired by Home Alone'
OL,6,FShe added: "The prosecution case is
OL,7,Fthat Mr Claughton had sought to
OL,8,Fprotect those drugs and the cash by
OL,9,Fthe possession of firearms and by the
OL,10,Flaying of traps - those traps
OL,11,Fincluding the use of some minor
OL,12,Fexplosives.
OL,14,F"The activities of Mr Claughton and
OL,15,FMrs Claughton had, it would appear,
OL,16,Fbrought trouble to their doors and Mr
OL,17,FClaughton attempted to deal with that
OL,18,Ftrouble by fortifying the property and
OL,19,Farming himself against any would-be
OL,21,Fintruders."
