OL,3,CMan who set up traps and explosives
OL,4,C'inspired by Home Alone'
OL,6,FMs Chapman described how, when police
OL,7,Fentered one of the houses, "they noted
OL,8,Fa fishing wire running across the
OL,9,Flength of one of the rooms on the rear
OL,10,Ffloor".
OL,12,FShe said it was at knee height,
OL,13,Fattached to an electrical connector
OL,14,Fand a battery pack.
OL,16,FShe added that Ian Claughton told
OL,17,Fpolice the explosives were crow-
OL,18,Fscarers, used by farmers, which he had
OL,19,Finserted into plastic piping and, in
OL,20,Fone instance, into a bag of paint.
